https://leetcode.com/problems/word-ladder/description/


QUESTION:
Input: beginWord = "hit", endWord = "cog", wordList = ["hot","dot","dog","lot","log","cog"]
Output: 5
Explanation: One shortest transformation sequence is "hit" -> "hot" -> "dot" -> "dog" -> cog", which is 5 words long.
SOLUTION:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TIME  COMPLEXITY:O(N*L) where n is number of words in the list and L is length of each word.
SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(N*L)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Step 1: Create a Pair to store (word, steps) and initialize queue with (beginWord, 1)
Step 2: Create a HashSet and store all words from the wordList
Step 3: Remove beginWord from the set (to mark it visited)
Step 4: While the queue is not empty, pop the front element and get word and steps
Step 5: If the word is equal to endWord, return the steps
Step 6: Traverse each character index of the word
Step 7: For each index, try replacing it with characters from 'a' to 'z'
Step 8: Form a new word after replacement
Step 9: If the new word exists in the set, add it to the queue with steps + 1
Step 10: Remove that word from the set (mark as visited)
Step 11: Restore the original character before moving to next position
Step 12: If queue becomes empty and endWord is not found, return 0

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CODE:
class Solution {
    class Pair {
    String word;
    int steps;

    Pair(String word, int steps) {
        this.word = word;
        this.steps = steps;
    }
}
    public int ladderLength(String beginWord, String endWord, List<String> wordList) {
        Queue<Pair>q=new LinkedList<>();
        q.add(new Pair(beginWord,1));
        Set<String>set=new HashSet<>(wordList);
        set.remove(beginWord);
        while(!q.isEmpty()){
            Pair p = q.peek();
            String word = p.word;
            int step = p.steps;
            q.poll();
            if(word.equals(endWord))return step;
            for(int i=0;i<word.length();i++){
                char arr[]=word.toCharArray();
                char original=arr[i];
                for(char ch='a';ch<='z';ch++){
                    arr[i]=ch;
                    String newWord=new String(arr);
                    if(set.contains(newWord)){
                        set.remove(newWord);
                        q.add(new Pair(newWord,step+1));
                    }
                }
                arr[i]=original;
            }
        }

      return 0;
    }
}
